  <div>
    <h2>What is it?</h2>
    <p>The application "Style Guide" is an online reference for the Information Technology (IT) department at Foxtel.</p>
    <p>This guide aims to:</p>
    <ul class="Bulleted">
      <li>Ensure correctness and consistency for Customer Systems Internal Applications.</li>
      <li>Establish standards for clear and consistent mark-up.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If you cannot find what you are looking for, or if you have any additional questions, comments or suggestions for this guide, please contact the Customer Systems UX Team.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>The Style Guide navigation categorizes different UI controls by their presentation and function. Under each category you will be able to find example controls, along with snippets of HTML, CSS and Javascript that can be referenced.</p>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <div>
    <h2>Integration</h2>
    <p class="Alert">Make sure you build a release version of the style guide first using "grunt dist".</p>
    <br />
    <div class="TabContainer">
      <div class="TabGroup">
        <ul class="Tabs">
          <li class="Active"><a href="#CORE">CORE</a></li>
          <li><a href="#RMS">RMS</a></li>
        </ul>
        <div id="CORE" class="TabContent">
          <p><b>Copy CSS and JS files from the Distribution List folders into corresponding Core folders:</b></p>
          <ul class="Bulleted">
            <li>
              CSS files - Found under <b>...\dist\css\</b>
              <ol>
                <li>foxtel.min.css</li>
                <li>foxtelHacks.min.css</li>
                <li>foxtelIE.min.css</li>
              </ol>
              <p>Into <b>...\ootbworkspace\web-commons\base\web\include\css\</b></p>
            </li>
            <li>
              JS files - Found under <b>...\dist\scripts\</b>
              <ol>
                <li>foxtel.min.js</li>
                <li>polyfills.min.js</li>
              </ol>
              <p>Into<b>...\ootbworkspace\web-commons\base\web\include\js\</b></p>
            </li>
          </ul>        
        </div>
        <div id="RMS" class="TabContent">
          <p>Details to be provided</p>
